<p>The more people realise that it's just complimentary skillsets and that working <strong>together</strong> is a far more efficient way of getting things done.</p>
<p>What I would say is that those skillsets need to be respected <em>and</em> when outside of your own particular skillset it's a good opportunity to learn from others. This of course requires an open mind, something that is missing in many areas of society these days...
